OBJECT

  INPUT (TLS)
  OUTPUT (FFMPEG RTMP LISTEN)
  STATUS (NOCONN, CONN, DISCONN)


CONTROL


TLS CONNECTION (INPUT)

  SERVER LISTEN
    ON CONNECTION PER SERVER

  GET RTMPS SOCKET
  PAUSE
  TCP CONNECT TO FFMPEG RTMP
  SETUP PIPE

  CLEAN ON END


SPAWN FFMPEG RTMP

  SPAWN (ffmpeg -listen 1 -i rtmp://127.0.0.1:xxxx)
  TCP CONNECT FROM TLS
  SETUP PIPE

  CLEAN ON END


TCP/TLS CONNECTION (OUTPUT)

  SERVER LISTEN
    ON CONNECTION PER SERVER

    CLEAN ON END












TLS	>	TCP	>	FFMPEG	>	TCP
		<			<				
